      "description": "Offered is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six. This high-revving power unit utilizes individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver linear power delivery up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory variable M-differential lock. The chassis remains taut, benefiting from a recent subframe reinforcement\u2014a critical preventative measure for this platform. Suspension components include MacPherson struts up front and a multi-link rear setup, providing exceptional lateral grip and communicative feedback. The braking system features cross-drilled rotors with refreshed calipers for consistent thermal management. This example is mechanically sound, showing well-maintained compression and a clean oil analysis, making it a driver-focused machine ready for the canyons or the track.",
